what career would suit my personality i'm really trying to figure out what i want to do with my life it used to seem so clear but it seems within the last years i've become really confused i couldn't ever see myself doing a job where everything is the same routine constantly it would drive me crazy i have to have change or i get really overwhelmed and depressed i do like traveling but i don't think that's something i would want to do all the time i would want to have a home to go to i want to have a husband eventually maybe children not sure i love writing but if i'm not personally inspired by the topic i find it to be very boring i work best at everything if i'm passionate about it personality traits friendly people person can be convincing level headed spontaneous good at writing love it creativity wants to help people extremely accepting of most people genuine driven can have days when i just need a break career suggestions anyone also i don't think i would be interested in something that requires many years of school i never really like the whole school thing boring routine even though i did well another trait i thought of competitive journalism has crossed my mind but i don't know the pay isn't always great perhaps you could be good at sales or try taking a few aptitude tests and see what they suggest you do here's one where they offer jobs at the end http gsx com freeaptitest htm then just spend a few days searching google for more aptitude tests and by the end i am sure you'll have a few ideas there are a few more here http www job listings info have fun Social rule Milton H. Erickson Scientology beliefs and practices Friends One Tree Hill (TV series) Pitaten Spice Girls Autism Personality psychology Myers-Briggs Type Indicator Charmed EastEnders The Smoking Room Reincarnation World Wide Web Graduate school Knots Landing Great Teacher Onizuka Borderline personality disorder Procrastination Strategic management Great Depression Kurt Cobain Eternal Sunshine of 